obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (6413)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6413&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called ^1[the Pre-conception and`
  line `Pre-natal Diagnostic Techniques (Prohibition of Sex Selection)] Act, 1994.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall extend to the whole of India ^2***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^3 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "the Pre-natal Diagnostic Techniques (Regulation and Prevention of Misuse)" (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `3. 1st January, 1996, vide notification No. S.O. 990, dated 21st December, 1995, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (6414)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6414&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) "Appropriate Authority" means the Appropriate Authority appointed under section 17;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board" means the Central Supervisory Board constituted under section 7;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(ba) "conceptus" means any product of conception at any stage of development from`
  line `fertilisation until birth including extra embryonic membranes as well as the embryo or foetus;`
  line
  line `(bb) "embryo" means a developing human organism after fertilisation till the end of eight weeks`
  line `(fifty-six days);`
  line
  line `(bc) "foetus" means a human organism during the period of its development beginning on the`
  line `fifty-seventh day following fertilisation or creation (excluding any time in which its development has`
  line `been suspended) and ending at the birth;]`
  line
  line `(c) "Genetic Counselling Centre" means an institute, hospital, nursing home or any place, by`
  line `whatever name called, which provides for genetic counselling to patients;`
  line
  line `(d) "Genetic Clinic" means a clinic, institute, hospital, nursing home or any place, by whatever`
  line `name called, which is used for conducting pre-natal diagnostic procedures.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Explanation. - For the purposes of this clause, "Genetic Clinic" includes a vehicle, where`
  line `ultrasound machine or imaging machine or scanner or other equipment capable of determining sex of`
  line `the foetus or a portable equipment which has the potential for detection of sex during pregnancy or`
  line `selection of sex before conception, is used;]`
  line
  line `(e) "Genetic Laboratory" means a laboratory and includes a place where facilities are provided`
  line `for conducting analysis or tests of samples received from Genetic Clinic for pre-natal diagnostic test.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Explanation. --For the purposes of this clause, "Genetic Laboratory" includes a place where`
  line `ultrasound machine or imaging machine or scanner or other equipment capable of determining sex of`
  line `the foetus or a portable equipment which has the potential for detection of sex during pregnancy or`
  line `selection of sex before conception, is used;]`
  line
  line `(f) "gynaecologist" means a person who possesses a post-graduate qualification in gynaecology`
  line `and obstetrics;`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(g) "medical geneticist" includes a person who possesses a degree or diploma in genetic science`
  line `in the fields of sex selection and pre-natal diagnostic techniques or has experience of not less than two`
  line `years in any of these fields after obtaining--`
  line
  line `(i) any one of the medical qualifications recognised under the Indian Medical Council Act,`
  line `1956 (102 of 1956); or`
  line
  line `(ii) a post-graduate degree in biological sciences;]`
  line
  line `(h) "paediatrician" means a person who possesses a post-graduate qualification in paediatrics;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(i) "pre-natal diagnostic procedures" means all gynaecological or obstetrical or medical`
  line `procedures such as ultrasonography, foetoscopy, taking or removing samples of amniotic fluid,`
  line `chorionic villi, embryo, blood or any other tissue or fluid of a man, or of a woman before or after`
  line `conception, for being sent to a Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic for conducting any type of`
  line `analysis or pre-natal diagnostic tests for selection of sex before or after conception;]`
  line
  line `(j) "pre-natal diagnostic techniques" includes all pre-natal diagnostic procedures and pre-natal`
  line `diagnostic tests;`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(k) "pre-natal diagnostic test" means ultrasonography or any test or analysis of amniotic fluid,`
  line `chorionic villi, blood or any tissue or fluid of a pregnant woman or conceptus conducted to detect`
  line `genetic or metabolic disorders or chromosomal abnormalities or congenital anomalies or`
  line `haemoglobinopathies or sex- linked diseases;]`
  line
  line `(l) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "registered medical practitione"r means a medical practitioner who possesses any recognised`
  line `medical qualification as defined in clause (h) of section 2 of the Indian Medical Council Act, 1956`
  line `(102 of 1956), and whose name has been entered in a State Medical Register;`
  line
  line `(n) "regulations" means regulations framed by the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line ^6
  line `[(o) "sex selection" includes any procedure, technique, test or administration or prescription or`
  line `provision of anything for the purpose of ensuring or increasing the probability that an embryo will be`
  line `of a particular sex;`
  line
  line `(p) "sonologist or imaging specialist" means a person who possesses any one of the medical`
  line `qualifications recognised under the Indian Medical Council Act, 1956 (102 of 1956) or who possesses`
  line `a post-graduate qualification in ultrasonography or imaging techniques or radiology;`
  line
  line `(q) "State Board" means a State Supervisory Board or a Union territory Supervisory Board`
  line `constituted under section 16A;`
  line
  line `(r) "State Government" in relation to Union territory with Legislature means the Administrator of`
  line `that Union territory appointed by the President under article 239 of the Constitution.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 4 (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  line
  line `2 Added by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 4, for clause (g) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  line
  line `4 Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (i) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  line
  line `5 Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (k) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  line
  line `6 Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (6415)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Regulation of Genetic Counselling Centres, Genetic Laboratories and Genetic Clinics.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `10 Subs. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 5, for clause (2) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6415&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line On
  line `and from the commencement of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(1) no Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic unless registered under`
  line `this Act, shall conduct or associate with, or help in, conducting activities relating to pre-natal`
  line `diagnostic techniques;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) no Genetic Counselling Centre or Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic shall employ or`
  line `cause to be employed or take services of any person, whether on honorary basis or on payment who`
  line `does not possess the qualifications as may be prescribed;]`
  line
  line `(3) no medical geneticist, gynaecologist paediatrician registered medical practitioner or any other`
  line `person shall conduct or cause to be conducted or aid in conducting by himself or through any other`
  line `person, any pre-natal diagnostic techniques at a place other than a place registered under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (6416)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Prohibition of sex selection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6416&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[3A. Prohibition of sex selection.--No person, including a specialist or a team of specialists in the`
  line `field of infertility, shall conduct or cause to be conducted or aid in conducting by himself or by any other`
  line `person, sex selection on a woman or a man or on both or on any tissue, embryo, conceptus, fluid or`
  line `gametes derived from either or both of them.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_b:
  sectionId (6417)
  sectionNo 3B
  orderNo 5
  title `Prohibition on sale of ultrasound machine, etc., to persons, laboratories, etc., not registered under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_b_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6417&sectionno=3B&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_3_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[3B. Prohibition on sale of ultrasound machine, etc., to persons, laboratories, clinics, etc., not`
  line `registered under the Act.--No person shall sell any ultrasound machine or imaging machine or scanner`
  line `or any other equipment capable of detecting sex of the foetus to any Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic`
  line `Laboratory, Genetic Clinic or any other person not registered under the Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (6418)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 6
  title `Regulation of pre-natal diagnostic techniques.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for clauses (3) and (4) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6418&sectionno=4&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On and from the commencement of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(1) no place including a registered Genetic Counselling Centre or Genetic Laboratory or Genetic`
  line `Clinic shall be used or caused to be used by any person for conducting pre-natal diagnostic techniques`
  line `except for the purposes specified in clause (2) and after satisfying any of the conditions specified in`
  line `clause (3);`
  line
  line `(2) no pre-natal diagnostic techniques shall be conducted except for the purposes of detection of`
  line `any of the following abnormalities, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) chromosomal abnormalities;`
  line
  line `(ii) genetic metabolic diseases;`
  line
  line `(iii) haemoglobinopathies;`
  line
  line `(iv) sex-linked genetic diseases;`
  line
  line `(v) congenital anomalies;`
  line
  line `(vi) any other abnormalities or diseases as may be specified by the Central Supervisory`
  line Board;
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(3) no pre-natal diagnostic techniques shall be used or conducted unless the person qualified to`
  line `do so is satisfied for reasons to be recorded in writing that any of the following conditions are`
  line `fulfilled, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) age of the pregnant woman is above thirty-five years;`
  line
  line `(ii) the pregnant woman has undergone two or more spontaneous abortions or foetal loss;`
  line
  line `(iii) the pregnant woman had been exposed to potentially teratogenic agents such as drugs,`
  line `radiation, infection or chemicals;`
  line
  line `(iv) the pregnant woman or her spouse has a family history of mental retardation or physical`
  line `deformities such as, spasticity or any other genetic disease;`
  line
  line `(v) any other condition as may be specified by the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person conducting ultrasonography on a pregnant woman shall keep complete`
  line `record thereof in the clinic in such manner, as may be prescribed, and any deficiency or inaccuracy found therein shall amount to contravention of the provisions of section 5 or section 6 unless contrary`
  line `is proved by the person conducting such ultrasonography;`
  line
  line `(4) no person including a relative or husband of the pregnant woman shall seek or encourage the`
  line `conduct of any pre-natal diagnostic techniques on her except for the purposes specified in clause (2);`
  line
  line `(5) no person including a relative or husband of a woman shall seek or encourage the conduct of`
  line `any sex selection technique on her or him or both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (6419)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 7
  title `Written consent of pregnant woman and prohibition of communicating the sex of foetus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 8, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6419&sectionno=5&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `No person referred to in clause (2) of section 3 shall conduct the pre-natal diagnostic procedures unless--`
  line
  line `(a) he has explained all known side and after effects of such procedures to the pregnant woman`
  line concerned;
  line
  line `(b) he has obtained in the prescribed form her written consent to undergo such procedures in the`
  line `language which she understands; and`
  line
  line `(c) a copy of her written consent obtained under clause (b) is given to the pregnant woman.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) No person including the person conducting pre-natal diagnostic procedures shall communicate`
  line `to the pregnant woman concerned or her relatives or any other person the sex of the foetus by words,`
  line `signs, or in any other manner.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (6420)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 8
  title `Determination of sex prohibited.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6420&sectionno=6&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `On and from the commencement of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) no Genetic Counselling Centre or Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic shall conduct or cause`
  line `to be conducted in its Centre, Laboratory or Clinic, pre-natal diagnostic techniques including`
  line `ultrasonography, for the purpose of determining the sex of a foetus;`
  line
  line `(b) no person shall conduct or cause to be conducted any pre-natal diagnostic techniques`
  line `including ultrasonography for the purpose of determining the sex of a foetus;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(c) no person shall, by whatever means, cause or allow to be caused selection of sex before or`
  line `after conception.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (6421)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 9
  title `Constitution of Central Supervisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6421&sectionno=7&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall constitute a`
  line `Board to be known as the Central Supervisory Board to exercise the powers and perform the functions`
  line `conferred on the Board under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Minister in charge of the Ministry or Department of Family Welfare, who shall be the`
  line `Chairman, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) the Secretary to the Government of India in charge of the Department of Family Welfare, who`
  line `shall be the Vice-Chairman, ex officio;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(c) three members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the Ministries of`
  line `Central Government in charge of Women and Child Development, Department of Legal Affairs or`
  line `Legislative Department in the Ministry of Law and Justice, and Indian System of Medicine and`
  line `Homoeopathy, ex officio;]`
  line
  line `(d) the Director General of Health Services of the Central Government, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) ten members to be appointed by the Central Government, two each from amongst--`
  line
  line `(i) eminent medical geneticists;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ii) eminent gynaecologist and obstetrician or expert of stri-roga or prasuti-tantra.]`
  line
  line `(iii) eminent paediatricians;`
  line
  line `(iv) eminent social scientists; and`
  line
  line `(v) representatives of women welfare organisations;`
  line
  line `(f) three women Members of Parliament, of whom two shall be elected by the House of the`
  line `People and one by the Council of States;`
  line
  line `(g) four members to be appointed by the Central Government by rotation to represent the States`
  line `and the Union territories, two in the alphabetical order and two in the reverse alphabetical order:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appointment under this clause shall be made except on the recommendation of`
  line `the State Government or, as the case may be, the Union territory;`
  line
  line `(h) an officer, not below the rank of a Joint Secretary or equivalent of the Central Government, in`
  line `charge of Family Welfare, who shall be the Member-Secretary, ex officio.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  line `2 Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (6422)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 10
  title `Term of office of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6422&sectionno=8&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term of office of a member, other than an ex officio`
  line `member, shall be,--`
  line
  line `(a) in case of appointment under clause (e) or clause (f) of sub-section (2) of section 7, three`
  line `years: ^1`
  line ***
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Provided that the term of office of a member elected under clause (f) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 7 shall come to an end as soon as the member becomes a Minister or Minister of State or`
  line `Deputy Minister, or the Speaker or the Deputy Speaker of the House of the People, or the Deputy`
  line `Chairman of the Council of States or ceases to be a member of the House from which she was`
  line `elected; and]`
  line
  line `(b) in case of appointment under clause (g) of the said sub-section, one year.`
  line
  line `(2) If a casual vacancy occurs in the office of any other members, whether by reason of his death,`
  line `resignation or inability to discharge his functions owing to illness or other incapacity, such vacancy shall`
  line `be filled by the Central Government by making a fresh appointment and the member so appointed shall`
  line `hold office for the remainder of the term of office of the person in whose place he is so appointed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Vice-Chairman shall perform such functions as may be assigned to him by the Chairman`
  line `from time to time.`
  line
  line `(4) The procedure to be followed by the members in the discharge of their functions shall be such as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "and" omitted by Act 32 of 2001, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-9-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (6423)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `Meetings of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6423&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall meet at such time and place, and shall observe such`
  line `rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at such`
  line `meetings) as may be provided by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall meet at least once in six months.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman and in his absence the Vice-Chairman shall preside at the meetings of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) If for any reason the Chairman or the Vice-Chairman is unable to attend any meeting of the Board,`
  line `any other member chosen by the members present at the meeting shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority of`
  line `the votes of the members present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairman, or in`
  line `his absence, the person presiding, shall have and exercise a second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(5) Members other than ex officio members shall receive such allowances, if any, from the Board as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (6424)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6424&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Board shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Board; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Board not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (6425)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Temporary association of persons with the Board for particular purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes '`````````````````'
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6425&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board`
  line `may associate with itself, in such manner and for such purposes as may be determined by regulations, any`
  line `person whose assistance or advice it may desire in carrying out any of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A person associated with it by the Board under sub-section (1) for any purpose shall have a right`
  line `to take part in the discussions relevant to that purpose, but shall not have a right to vote at a meeting of`
  line `the Board and shall not be a member for any other purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (6426)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Appointment of officers and other employees of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6426&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of enabling it`
  line `efficiently to discharge its functions under this Act, the Board may, subject to such regulations as may be`
  line `made in this behalf, appoint (whether on deputation or otherwise) such number of officers and other`
  line `employees as it may consider necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appointment of such category of officers, as may be specified in such regulations,`
  line `shall be subject to the approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every officer or other employee appointed by the Board shall be subject to such conditions of`
  line `service and shall be entitled to such remuneration as may be specified in the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (6427)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Authentication of orders and other instruments of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6427&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions of the`
  line `Board shall be authenticated by the signature of the Chairman or any other member authorised by the`
  line `Board in this behalf, and all other instruments issued by the Board shall be authenticated by the signature`
  line `of the Member-Secretary or any other officer of the Board authorised in like manner in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (6428)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Disqualifications for appointment as member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 11, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6428&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified for being`
  line `appointed as a member if, he--`
  line
  line `(a) has been convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(b) is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(c) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(d) has been removed or dismissed from the service of the Government or a Corporation owned`
  line `or controlled by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(e) has, in the opinion of the Central Government, such financial or other interest in the Board as`
  line `is likely to affect prejudicially the discharge by him of his functions as a member; or`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(f) has, in the opinion of the Central Government, been associated with the use or promotion of`
  line `pre-natal diagnostic technique for determination of sex or with any sex selection technique.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (6429)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Eligibility of member for reappointment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-9-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6429&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the other terms and conditions of service`
  line `as may be prescribed, any person ceasing to be a member shall be eligible for reappointment as such`
  line `member:`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided that no member other than an ex officio member shall be appointed for more than two`
  line `consecutive terms.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (6430)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Functions of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for section 16 (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6430&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[16. Functions of the Board.-- The Board shall have the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) to advise the Central Government on policy matters relating to use of pre-natal diagnostic`
  line `techniques, sex selection techniques and against their misuse;`
  line
  line `(ii) to review and monitor implementation of the Act and rules made thereunder and recommend`
  line `to the Central Government changes in the said Act and rules;`
  line
  line `(iii) to create public awareness against the practice of pre-conception sex selection and pre-natal`
  line `determination of sex of foetus leading to female foeticide;`
  line
  line `(iv) to lay down code of conduct to be observed by persons working at Genetic Counselling`
  line `Centres, Genetic Laboratories and Genetic Clinics;`
  line
  line `(v) to oversee the performance of various bodies constituted under the Act and take appropriate`
  line `steps to ensure its proper and effective implementation;`
  line
  line `(vi) any other functions as may be prescribed under the Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (6431)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 19
  title `Constitution of State Supervisory Board and Union territory Supervisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 14 (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6431&sectionno=16A&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[16A. Constitution of State Supervisory Board and Union territory Supervisory`
  line `Board.--(1) Each State and Union territory having Legislature shall constitute a Board to be known as`
  line `the State Supervisory Board or the Union territory Supervisory Board, as the case may be, which shall`
  line `have the following functions:--`
  line
  line `(i) to create public awareness against the practice of pre-conception sex selection and pre-natal`
  line `determination of sex of the foetus leading to female foeticide in the State;`
  line
  line `(ii) to review the activities of the Appropriate Authorities functioning in the State and recommend`
  line `appropriate action against them;`
  line
  line `(iii) to monitor the implementation of provisions of the Act and the rules and make suitable`
  line `recommendations relating thereto, to the Board;`
  line
  line `(iv) to send such consolidated reports as may be prescribed in respect of the various activities`
  line `undertaken in the State under the Act to the Board and the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(v) any other functions as may be prescribed under the Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Board shall consist of,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Minister in charge of Health and Family Welfare in the State, who shall be the`
  line `Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) Secretary in charge of the Department of Health and Family Welfare who shall be the`
  line `Vice-Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) Secretaries or Commissioners in charge of Departments of Women and Child Development,`
  line `Social Welfare, Law and Indian System of Medicines and Homoeopathy, ex officio, or their`
  line representatives;
  line
  line `(d) Director of Health and Family Welfare or Indian System of Medicines and Homoeopathy of`
  line `the State Government, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) three women members of Legislative Assembly or Legislative Council;`
  line
  line `(f) ten members to be appointed by the State Government out of which two each shall be from the`
  line `following categories,--`
  line
  line `(i) eminent social scientists and legal experts;`
  line
  line `(ii) eminent women activists from non- governmental organisations or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(iii) eminent gynaecologists and obstetricians or experts of stri-roga or prasuti-tantra;`
  line
  line `(iv) eminent paediatricians or medical geneticists;`
  line
  line `(v) eminent radiologists or sonologists;`
  line
  line `(g) an officer not below the rank of Joint Director in charge of Family Welfare, who shall be the`
  line `Member Secretary, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Board shall meet at least once in four months.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of a member, other than an ex officio member, shall be three years.`
  line
  line `(5) If a vacancy occurs in the office of any member other than an ex officio member, it shall be filled`
  line `by making fresh appointment.`
  line
  line `(6) If a member of the Legislative Assembly or member of the Legislative Council who is a member`
  line `of the State Board, becomes Minister or Speaker or Deputy Speaker of the Legislative Assembly or`
  line `Chairperson or Deputy Chairperson of the Legislative Council, she shall cease to be a member of the`
  line `State Board.`
  line
  line `(7) One-third of the total number of members of the State Board shall constitute the quorum.`
  line
  line `(8) The State Board may co-opt a member as and when required, provided that the number of`
  line `co-opted members does not exceed one-third of the total strength of the State Board.`
  line
  line `(9) The co-opted members shall have the same powers and functions as other members, except the`
  line `right to vote and shall abide by the rules and regulations.`
  line
  line `(10) In respect of matters not specified in this section, the State Board shall follow procedures and`
  line `conditions as are applicable to the Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (6432)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 20
  title `Appropriate Authority and Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6432&sectionno=17&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, one or more Appropriate Authorities for each of the Union`
  line `territories for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall appoint, by notification in the Official Gazette, one or more`
  line `Appropriate Authorities for the whole or part of the State for the purposes of this Act having regard to the`
  line `intensity of the problem of pre-natal sex determination leading to female foeticide.`
  line
  line `(3) The officers appointed as Appropriate Authorities under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall`
  line be,--
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(a) when appointed for the whole of the State or the Union territory, consisting of the following`
  line `three members--`
  line
  line `(i) an officer of or above the rank of the Joint Director of Health and Family`
  line Welfare--Chairperson;
  line
  line `(ii) an eminent woman representing women's organisation; and`
  line
  line `(iii) an officer of Law Department of the State or the Union territory concerned:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be the duty of the State or the Union territory concerned to constitute`
  line `multi-member State or Union territory level Appropriate Authority within three months of the coming`
  line `into force of the Pre-natal Diagnostic Techniques (Regulation and Prevention of Misuse) Amendment`
  line `Act, 2002 (14 of 2003):`
  line
  line `Provided further that any vacancy occurring therein shall be filled within three months of the`
  line occurrence.]
  line
  line `(b) when appointed for any part of the State or the Union territory, of such other rank as the State`
  line `Government or the Central Government, as the case may be, may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appropriate Authority shall have the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to grant, suspend or cancel registration of a Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory`
  line `or Genetic Clinic;`
  line
  line `(b) to enforce standards prescribed for the Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory and`
  line `Genetic Clinic;`
  line
  line `(c) to investigate complaints of breach of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder`
  line `and take immediate action; and`
  line
  line `(d) to seek and consider the advice of the Advisory Committee, constituted under sub-section (5),`
  line `on application for registration and on complaints for suspension or cancellation of registration;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(e) to take appropriate legal action against the use of any sex selection technique by any person`
  line `at any place, suo motu or brought to its notice and also to initiate independent investigations in such`
  line matter;
  line
  line `(f) to create public awareness against the practice of sex selection or pre-natal determination of`
  line sex;
  line
  line `(g) to supervise the implementation of the provisions of the Act and rules;`
  line
  line `(h) to recommend to the Board and State Boards modifications required in the rules in accordance`
  line `with changes in technology or social conditions;`
  line
  line `(i) to take action on the recommendations of the Advisory Committee made after investigation of`
  line `complaint for suspension or cancellation of registration.]`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, shall constitute an`
  line `Advisory Committee for each Appropriate Authority to aid and advise the Appropriate Authority in the`
  line `discharge of its functions, and shall appoint one of the members of the Advisory Committee to be its`
  line Chairman.
  line
  line `(6) The Advisory Committee shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) three medical experts from amongst gynaecologists, obstericians, paediatricians and medical`
  line geneticists;
  line
  line `(b) one legal expert;`
  line
  line `(c) one officer to represent the department dealing with information and publicity of the State`
  line `Government or the Union territory, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(d) three eminent social workers of whom not less than one shall be from amongst representatives`
  line `of women's organisations.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(7) No person who has been associated with the use or promotion of pre-natal diagnostic techniques`
  line `for determination of sex or sex selection shall be appointed as a member of the Advisory Committee.]`
  line
  line `(8) The Advisory Committee may meet as and when it thinks fit or on the request of the Appropriate`
  line `Authority for consideration of any application for registration or any complaint for suspension or`
  line `cancellation of registration and to give advice thereon:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period intervening between any two meetings shall not exceed the prescribed`
  line period.
  line
  line `(9) The terms and conditions subject to which a person may be appointed to the Advisory Committee`
  line `and the procedure to be followed by such Committee in the discharge of its functions shall be such as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 15, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 15 (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for sub-section (7) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003)`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (6433)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 21
  title `Powers of Appropriate Authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6433&sectionno=17A&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[17A. Powers of Appropriate Authorities.--The Appropriate Authority shall have the powers in`
  line `respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning of any person who is in possession of any information relating to violation of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) production of any document or material object relating to clause (a);`
  line
  line `(c) issuing search warrant for any place suspected to be indulging in sex selection techniques or`
  line `pre-natal sex determination; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (6434)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title `Registration of Genetic Counselling Centres, Genetic Laboratories or Genetic Clinics.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 17, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6434&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) No person shall open any Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory or Genetic`
  line `Clinic, including clinic, laboratory or centre having ultrasound or imaging machine or scanner or any`
  line `other technology capable of undertaking determination of sex of foetus and sex selection, or render`
  line `services to any of them, after the commencement of the Pre-natal Diagnostic Techniques (Regulation and`
  line `Prevention of Misuse) Amendment Act, 2002 (14 of 2003) unless such Centre, Laboratory or Clinic is`
  line `duly registered under the Act.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for registration under sub-section (1), shall be made to the Appropriate`
  line `Authority in such form and in such manner and shall be accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic engaged, either partly or`
  line `exclusively, in counselling or conducting pre-natal diagnostic techniques for any of the purposes`
  line `mentioned in section 4, immediately before the commencement of this Act, shall apply for registration`
  line `within sixty days from the date of such commencement.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of section 6, every Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory or`
  line `Genetic Clinic engaged in counselling or conducting pre-natal diagnostic techniques shall cease to`
  line `conduct any such counselling or technique on the expiry of six months from the date of commencement`
  line `of this Act unless such Centre, Laboratory or Clinic has applied for registration and is so registered`
  line `separately or jointly or till such application is disposed of, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(5) No Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic shall be registered under`
  line `this Act unless the Appropriate Authority is satisfied that such Centre, Laboratory or Clinic is in a`
  line `position to provide such facilities, maintain such equipment and standards as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (6435)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 23
  title `Certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6435&sectionno=19&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appropriate Authority shall, after holding an inquiry and`
  line `after satisfying itself that the applicant has complied with all the requirements of this Act and the rules`
  line `made thereunder and having regard to the advice of the Advisory Committee in this behalf, grant a`
  line `certificate of registration in the prescribed form jointly or separately to the Genetic Counselling Centre,`
  line `Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) If, after the inquiry and after giving an opportunity of being heard to the applicant and having`
  line `regard to the advice of the Advisory Committee, the Appropriate Authority is satisfied that the applicant`
  line `has not complied with the requirements of this Act or the rules, it shall, for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, reject the application for registration.`
  line
  line `(3) Every certificate of registration shall be renewed in such manner and after such period and on`
  line `payment of such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The certificate of registration shall be displayed by the registered Genetic Counselling Centre,`
  line `Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic in a conspicuous place at its place of business.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (6436)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 24
  title `Cancellation or suspension of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6436&sectionno=20&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appropriate Authority may suo motu, or`
  line `on complaint, issue a notice to the Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic to`
  line `show cause why its registration should not be suspended or cancelled for the reasons mentioned in the`
  line notice.
  line
  line `(2) If, after giving a reasonable opportunity of being heard to the Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic`
  line `Laboratory or Genetic Clinic and having regard to the advice of the Advisory Committee, the Appropriate`
  line `Authority is satisfied that there has been a breach of the provisions of this Act or the rules, it may, without`
  line `prejudice to any criminal action that it may take against such Centre, Laboratory or Clinic, suspend its`
  line `registration for such period as it may think fit or cancel its registration, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), if the Appropriate Authority is of`
  line `the opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to do in the public interest, it may, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, suspend the registration of any Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory or`
  line `Genetic Clinic without issuing any such notice referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (6437)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 25
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6437&sectionno=21&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic may, within`
  line `thirty days from the date of receipt of the order of suspension or cancellation of registration passed by the`
  line `Appropriate Authority under section 20, prefer an appeal against such order to--`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Government, where the appeal is against the order of the Central Appropriate`
  line `Authority; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the State Government, where the appeal is against the order of the State Appropriate`
  line Authority,
  line
  line `in the prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (6438)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 26
  title `Prohibition of advertisement relating to pre-conception and pre-natal determination of sex and punishment for contravention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 18, for section 22 (w.e.f. 14-2-2003)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6438&sectionno=22&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[22. Prohibition of advertisement relating to pre-conception and pre-natal determination of sex`
  line `and punishment for contravention.-- (1) No person, organisation, Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic`
  line `Laboratory or Genetic Clinic including clinic, laboratory or centre having ultrasound machine or imaging`
  line `machine or scanner or any other technology capable of undertaking determination of sex of the foetus or`
  line `sex selection shall issue, publish, distribute, communicate or cause to be issued, published, distributed or`
  line `communicated any advertisement, in any form, including internet, regarding facilities of pre-natal`
  line `determination of sex or sex selection before conception available at such Centre, Laboratory, Clinic or at`
  line `any other place.`
  line
  line `(2) No person or organisation including Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory or Genetic`
  line `Clinic shall issue, publish, distribute, communicate or cause to be issued, published, distributed or`
  line `communicated any advertisement in any manner regarding pre-natal determination or pre-conception`
  line `selection of sex by any means whatsoever, scientific or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "advertisement" includes any notice, circular, label,`
  line `wrapper or any other document including advertisement through internet or any other media in electronic`
  line `or print form and also includes any visible representation made by means of any hoarding, wall-painting,`
  line `signal, light, sound, smoke or gas.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (6439)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 27
  title `Offences and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for sub-sections (2) and (3) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6439&sectionno=23&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any medical geneticist, gynaecologist, registered medical`
  line `practitioner or any person who owns a Genetic Counselling Centre, a Genetic Laboratory or a Genetic`
  line `Clinic or is employed in such a Centre, Laboratory or Clinic and renders his professional or technical`
  line `services to or at such a Centre, Laboratory or Clinic, whether on an honorary basis or otherwise, and who`
  line `contravenes any of the provisions of this Act or rules made thereunder shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and with fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees and on any subsequent conviction, with imprisonment which may extend to five years and with`
  line `fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The name of the registered medical practitioner shall be reported by the Appropriate Authority`
  line `to the State Medical Council concerned for taking necessary action including suspension of the`
  line `registration if the charges are framed by the court and till the case is disposed of and on conviction for`
  line `removal of his name from the register of the Council for a period of five years for the first offence and`
  line `permanently for the subsequent offence.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who seeks the aid of any Genetic Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory, Genetic`
  line `Clinic or ultrasound clinic or imaging clinic or of a medical geneticist, gynaecologist, sonologist or`
  line `imaging specialist or registered medical practitioner or any other person for sex selection or for`
  line `conducting pre-natal diagnostic techniques on any pregnant women for the purposes other than those`
  line `specified in sub-section (2) of section 4, he shall, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years and with fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees for the first offence and for`
  line `any subsequent offence with imprisonment which may extend to five years and with fine which may`
  line `extend to one lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby provided that the provisions of sub-section (3) shall not`
  line `apply to the woman who was compelled to undergo such diagnostic techniques or such selection.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (6440)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 28
  title `Presumption in the case of conduct of pre-natal diagnostic techniques.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 20, for section 24 (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6440&sectionno=24&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[24. Presumption in the case of conduct of pre-natal diagnostic techniques.-- Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), the court shall presume unless the`
  line `contrary is proved that the pregnant woman was compelled by her husband or any other relative, as the`
  line `case may be, to undergo pre-natal diagnostic technique for the purposes other than those specified in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 4 and such person shall be liable for abetment of offence under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 23 and shall be punishable for the offence specified under that section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (6441)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 29
  title `Penalty for contravention of the provisions of the Act or rules for which no specific punishment is provided.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6441&sectionno=25&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any of the provisions of this Act or any rules made`
  line `thereunder, for which no penalty has been elsewhere provided in this Act, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months or with fine, which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees or with both and in the case of continuing contravention with an additional fine which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees for every day during which such contravention continues after`
  line `conviction for the first such contravention.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (6442)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 30
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6442&sectionno=26&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any offence, punishable under this Act has been committed`
  line `by a company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence punishable under this`
  line `Act has been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary`
  line `or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to`
  line `be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) 'company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals,`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (6443)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 31
  title `Offence to be cognizable, non-bailable and non-compoundable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6443&sectionno=27&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Every offence under this Act`
  line `shall be cognizable, non-bailable and non-compoundable.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (6444)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 32
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for 'thirty days" (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6444&sectionno=28&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of an offence under this Act except`
  line `on a complaint made by`
  line
  line `(a) the Appropriate Authority concerned, or any officer authorised in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government or State Government, as the case may be, or the Appropriate Authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) a person who has given notice of not less than ^1[fifteen days] in the manner prescribed, to the`
  line `Appropriate Authority, of the alleged offence and of his intention to make a complaint to the court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purpose of this clause, "person" includes a social organisation.`
  line
  line `(2) No court other than that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class`
  line `shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a complaint has been made under clause (b) of sub-section (1), the court may, on demand`
  line `by such person, direct the Appropriate Authority to make available copies of the relevant records in its`
  line `possession to such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (6445)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 33
  title `Maintenance of records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6445&sectionno=29&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) All records, charts, forms, reports, consent letters and all other`
  line `documents required to be maintained under this Act and the rules shall be preserved for a period of two`
  line `years or for such period as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if any criminal or other proceedings are instituted against any Genetic Counselling`
  line `Centre, Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic, the records and all other documents of such Centre,`
  line `Laboratory or Clinic shall be preserved till the final disposal of such proceedings.`
  line
  line `(2) All such records shall, at all reasonable times, be made available for inspection to the Appropriate`
  line `Authority or to any other person authorised by the Appropriate Authority in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (6446)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to search and seize records, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 22, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6446&sectionno=30&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) If the Appropriate Authority has reason to`
  line `believe that an offence under this Act has been or is being committed at any Genetic Counselling Centre,`
  line `Genetic Laboratory, Genetic Clinic or any other place, such Authority or any officer authorised in this`
  line `behalf may, subject to such rules as may be prescribed, enter and search at all reasonable times with such`
  line `assistance, if any, as such Authority or officer considers necessary, such Genetic Counselling Centre,`
  line `Genetic Laboratory, Genetic Clinic or any other place and examine any record, register, document, book,`
  line `pamphlet, advertisement or any other material object found therein and seize and seal the same if such`
  line `Authority or officer has reason to believe that it may furnish evidence of the commission of an offence`
  line `punishable under this Act.]`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) relating to searches and`
  line `seizures shall, so far as may be, apply to every search or seizure made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (6447)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 35
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6447&sectionno=31&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central or the State Government or the Appropriate Authority or any officer authorised by`
  line `the Central or State Government or by the Authority for anything which is in good faith done or intended`
  line `to be done in pursuance of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (6448)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 36
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6448&sectionno=31A&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[31A. Removal of difficulties.-- (1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of the`
  line `Pre-natal Diagnostic Techniques (Regulation and Prevention of Misuse) Amendment Act, 2002`
  line `(14 of 2003), the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of the said Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient`
  line `for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of three years from`
  line `the date of commencement of the Pre-natal Diagnostic Techniques (Regulation and Prevention of Misuse)`
  line `Amendment Act, 2002 (14 of 2003).`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (6449)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6449&sectionno=32&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may make rules for carrying out the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(i) the minimum qualifications for persons employed at a registered Genetic Counselling`
  line `Centre, Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic under clause (2) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(ia) the manner in which the person conducting ultrasonography on a pregnant woman shall keep`
  line `record thereof in the clinic under the proviso to sub-section (3) of section 4;]`
  line
  line `(ii) the form in which consent of a pregnant woman has to be obtained under section 5;`
  line
  line `(iii) the procedure to be followed by the members of the Central Supervisory Board in the`
  line `discharge of their functions under sub-section (4) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(iv) allowances for members other than ex officio members admissible under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 9;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(iva) code of conduct to be observed by persons working at Genetic Counselling Centres,`
  line `Genetic Laboratories and Genetic Clinics to be laid down by the Central Supervisory Board under`
  line `clause (iv) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(ivb) the manner in which reports shall be furnished by the State and Union territory Supervisory`
  line `Boards to the Board and the Central Government in respect of various activities undertaken in the`
  line `State under the Act under clause (iv) of sub-section (1) of section 16A;`
  line
  line `(ivc) empowering the Appropriate Authority in any other matter under clause (d) of section 17A;]`
  line
  line `(v) the period intervening between any two meetings of the Advisory Committee under the`
  line `proviso to sub-section (8) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(vi) the terms and conditions subject to which a person may be appointed to the Advisory`
  line `Committee and the procedure to be followed by such Committee under sub-section (9) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(vii) the form and manner in which an application shall be made for registration and the fee`
  line `payable thereof under sub-section (2) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(viii) the facilities to be provided, equipment and other standards to be maintained by the Genetic`
  line `Counselling Centre, Genetic Laboratory or Genetic Clinic under sub-section (5) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(ix) the form in which a certificate of registration shall be issued under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 19;`
  line
  line `(x) the manner in which and the period after which a certificate of registration shall be renewed`
  line `and the fee payable for such renewal under sub-section (3) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(xi) the manner in which an appeal may be preferred under section 21;`
  line
  line `(xii) the period up to which records, charts, etc., shall be preserved under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 29;`
  line
  line `(xiii) the manner in which the seizure of documents, records, objects, etc., shall be made and the`
  line `manner in which seizure list shall be prepared and delivered to the person from whose custody such`
  line `documents, records or objects were seized under sub-section (1) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(xiv) any other matter that is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 24, ibid., for clause (i) (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 14 of 2003, s. 24 (w.e.f. 14-2-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (6450)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=6450&sectionno=33&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, with the previous sanction of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations not inconsistent with the provisions`
  line `of this Act and the rules made thereunder to provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the time and place of the meetings of the Board and the procedure to be followed for the`
  line `transaction of business at such meetings and the number of members which shall form the quorum`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which a person may be temporarily associated with the Board under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) the method of appointment, the conditions of service and the scales of pay and allowances of`
  line `the officer and other employees of the Board appointed under section 12;`
  line
  line `(d) generally for the efficient conduct of the affairs of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (12966)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 39
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443&sectionId=12966&sectionno=34&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00013_199457_1517807323443
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
